New Records: Buddy Hield broke his own record for most made threes in the first five games with a new team in NBA history
Key Match Events: The Golden State Warriors scored the first six points of the night and never looked back.
Draymond Green scored eight straight points in the second frame, knocking down two 3-pointers during his run.
Post-Match Reflections: Lindy Waters III got his first career start as a Warrior, finishing with three points and three assists with a plus-13 plus-minus.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Warriors closed out their three-game homestand and would open a five-game road trip on Saturday night against the Houston Rockets.
